data.content:
Three breaking changes hit your code. Here's each one and the fix:

---

### 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` — now accepts a regular lambda, not an expression tree

Your manual `Expression.Lambda` / `Expression.Call` tree **won't compile** because a new non-expression `Func<>` overload takes priority.

**Fix — replace the entire block:**
```csharp
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

No more expression-tree plumbing needed.

---

### 2. Complex type column names — now auto-uniquified & nested paths changed

Two sub-changes:

- **Uniquification:** `ShippingAddress.Street` and `BillingAddress.Street` previously shared one `Street` column (silent data corruption risk). EF 10 appends a suffix (`Street`, `Street1`).
- **Nested full path:** `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` previously mapped to `BillingAddress_City`. Now it becomes `Payment_BillingAddress_City`.

**Fix — pin the old names explicitly if you have an existing database:**
```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b =>
{
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress, p =>
        p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street"));
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress, p =>
        p.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("Street")); // only if you truly want sharing
});

// For nested complex types, pin each property:
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>()
    .ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment)
    .ComplexProperty(p => p.BillingAddress)
    .Property(a => a.City)
    .HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City");
```

Or simply **add a migration** and let it rename the columns to the new defaults.

---

### 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` — new `logCommandText` parameter

Every method gained a `string logCommandText` parameter (for redacted SQL logging).

**Fix — add the parameter:**
```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection,
        DbCommand command,
        DbContext context,
        Guid commandId,
        Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)   // ← new
    {
        // Use logCommandText for logging (sensitive data redacted)
        // Use command.CommandText for the real SQL
    }
}
```

Update **all** methods on the interface (`CommandReaderExecuted`, `CommandScalarExecuting`, etc.) the same way.
